Write a python program takes a number and finds the binary equivalent of a number recursively.

Input & Output Format:

#python
def convert(n):
    if n>1:
        convert(n//2)
    print(n%2,end="")
dec=int(input())
convert(dec)

Input consists of one integer.

Output consists of a binary number.

Sample Input:

5

Sample Output:

 1 0 1
 
 #python
def convert(n):
    if n>1:
        convert(n//2)
    print(n%2,end="")
dec=int(input())
convert(dec)
